[ ♪♪♪ ]

2
00:00:11,968 --> 00:00:13,491
[SCOOBY MUNCHING]

3
00:00:13,491 --> 00:00:14,971
Eee-Hee-Hee-Hee-Hee!

4
00:00:14,971 --> 00:00:17,974
♪ Scooby-Dooby-Doo
Where are you? ♪

5
00:00:17,974 --> 00:00:20,846
♪ We've got
some work to do now ♪

6
00:00:20,846 --> 00:00:23,632
♪ Scooby-Dooby-Doo
Where are you? ♪

7
00:00:23,632 --> 00:00:26,809
♪ We need some help
from you now ♪

8
00:00:31,901 --> 00:00:33,859
SCOOBY-DOO: Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

9
00:00:46,394 --> 00:00:47,917
[CACKLING]

10
00:00:47,917 --> 00:00:50,615
WOMAN: Let go of me!

11
00:00:50,615 --> 00:00:52,400
Okay, now I really have
a wedgie.

12
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:56,012
Fred! Velma!

13
00:00:56,012 --> 00:00:58,536
Can you guys hurry it up?
This ghost keeps grabbing--

14
00:01:00,321 --> 00:01:02,149
Please!

15
00:01:02,149 --> 00:01:03,541
Jinkies.

16
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:04,586
Fred.

17
00:01:04,586 --> 00:01:07,110
Come in, Fred.

18
00:01:07,110 --> 00:01:08,764
Fred!

Can you hear me?

19
00:01:08,764 --> 00:01:10,200
Fredster here, Velms.

20
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,768
Shockingly, Daphne's

been captured again.

21
00:01:12,768 --> 00:01:14,291
That's okay.

22
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:17,033
When the Luna Ghost
rounds the corner with Daphne,

23
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:19,905
Shaggy and Scooby
will pop out of the barrel--

24
00:01:19,905 --> 00:01:21,385
Then you'll activate
the conveyor belt,

25
00:01:21,385 --> 00:01:23,431
spilling the oil onto the floor.

26
00:01:23,431 --> 00:01:25,868
[LUNA GHOST GIGGLING]

27
00:01:25,868 --> 00:01:27,217
Just remember

my plan.

28
00:01:27,217 --> 00:01:29,524
SHAGGY: Like,
chill out, Scooby-Doo.

29
00:01:29,524 --> 00:01:31,308
Stop shaking.

30
00:01:31,308 --> 00:01:33,005
SCOOBY-DOO:
Me? That's you.

31
00:01:33,005 --> 00:01:34,616
Right. It's me.
Sorry.

32
00:01:34,616 --> 00:01:37,053
[LUNA GHOST GIGGLING]

33
00:01:37,053 --> 00:01:38,228
[SCOOBY-DOO YELPS]

34
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:44,495
[CLANG]

35
00:01:46,018 --> 00:01:47,281
Boo.

36
00:01:47,281 --> 00:01:49,152
Aagh!

37
00:01:49,152 --> 00:01:52,068
Scooby-Doo,
what are you doing, man?

38
00:01:52,068 --> 00:01:56,028
Like, this is
no time to...

39
00:01:56,028 --> 00:01:58,030
to...

40
00:01:58,030 --> 00:01:59,771
Oh, boy.

41
00:01:59,771 --> 00:02:01,991
Like, there's a ghost
right behind me, isn't there?

42
00:02:07,475 --> 00:02:08,911
Run!

43
00:02:16,397 --> 00:02:17,746
SCOOBY-DOO: Go away. Go!

44
00:02:17,746 --> 00:02:20,227
Run!

45
00:02:20,227 --> 00:02:22,577
SHAGGY: Like, I'm trying, buddy!

46
00:02:22,577 --> 00:02:24,579
SCOOBY-DOO: Try?

47
00:02:24,579 --> 00:02:26,494
Fred, now!

48
00:02:28,713 --> 00:02:29,714
FRED: I got him.

49
00:02:46,992 --> 00:02:48,516
Sorry, Velma.

50
00:02:48,516 --> 00:02:49,908
I know, Fred.

51
00:02:49,908 --> 00:02:50,996
Where's the ghost?

52
00:02:50,996 --> 00:02:52,737
He's right behind me.

53
00:02:52,737 --> 00:02:54,609
Skateboard!

54
00:02:54,609 --> 00:02:56,001
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

55
00:03:10,973 --> 00:03:12,453
Is he still after us, Scoob?

56
00:03:14,629 --> 00:03:15,630
Banzai!

57
00:03:21,157 --> 00:03:23,812
Zoinks! Grab the hook!

58
00:03:23,812 --> 00:03:25,248
Hold on, Shaggy!

59
00:03:41,482 --> 00:03:42,874
Daphne,
are you okay?

60
00:03:45,964 --> 00:03:47,488
I'm so over

61
00:03:47,488 --> 00:03:49,098
this damsel-in-distress
nonsense.

62
00:03:49,098 --> 00:03:50,273
Where's Shagster?

63
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:54,495
Like, I'm right here, man.

64
00:03:54,495 --> 00:03:55,496
Me too.

65
00:03:55,496 --> 00:03:57,019
Hey, Scoob, that was fun.

66
00:03:57,019 --> 00:03:58,499
Let's grab
another skateboard

67
00:03:58,499 --> 00:03:59,500
and do it again.

68
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,589
Yeah. Eee-Hee-Hee-Hee!

69
00:04:01,589 --> 00:04:02,546
[TIRES SCREECHING]

70
00:04:10,815 --> 00:04:12,948
[ROCK MUSIC]

71
00:04:20,129 --> 00:04:21,783
There you go.

72
00:04:21,783 --> 00:04:23,567
One for you.

73
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:25,569
Good-looking guy.

74
00:04:25,569 --> 00:04:26,962
All right, nice to see you.

75
00:04:26,962 --> 00:04:30,139
Thank you so much
for saving the factory.

76
00:04:30,139 --> 00:04:32,620
REPORTER:
Pam, any comments?

77
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,099
This is a victory
for any celebrity

78
00:04:34,099 --> 00:04:36,885
who wants to make
a quality action figure.

79
00:04:36,885 --> 00:04:38,930
What's the secret
of your success?

80
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:40,497
Teamwork.

81
00:04:40,497 --> 00:04:42,064
I do
a tremendous amount of teamwork,

82
00:04:42,064 --> 00:04:43,805
and...

83
00:04:43,805 --> 00:04:45,328
I always have a plan.

84
00:04:45,328 --> 00:04:47,852
Yeah...my plan.

85
00:04:47,852 --> 00:04:51,203
FRED: I knew from the beginning
there was never a phantom.

86
00:04:51,203 --> 00:04:52,727
The Luna Ghost is, in fact...

87
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:57,645
Old Man Smithers?

88
00:04:57,645 --> 00:04:59,473
The creepy janitor?

89
00:04:59,473 --> 00:05:01,649
Smithers wanted revenge after
you refused to go out with him.

90
00:05:01,649 --> 00:05:03,085
How could you, Pamela?

91
00:05:03,085 --> 00:05:04,695
I'm a lover-boy

92
00:05:04,695 --> 00:05:06,480
of George Clooney-an
proportions.

93
00:05:07,742 --> 00:05:09,091
REPORTER: Fred, how was
the ghost able to fly?

94
00:05:09,091 --> 00:05:10,527
I can answer that.

95
00:05:10,527 --> 00:05:12,181
Watch.

96
00:05:15,097 --> 00:05:16,751
These balloons fill

97
00:05:16,751 --> 00:05:19,754
with a highly potent
helium synthesis,

98
00:05:19,754 --> 00:05:21,712
giving the Luna Ghost...

99
00:05:23,061 --> 00:05:24,498
his weightless
appearance.

100
00:05:26,021 --> 00:05:28,763
I would have
gotten away with it too,

101
00:05:28,763 --> 00:05:31,243
if it weren't
for you meddling kids

102
00:05:31,243 --> 00:05:32,288
and your dumb dog!

103
00:05:32,288 --> 00:05:34,595
I'll get you for this!

104
00:05:34,595 --> 00:05:38,076
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

105
00:05:43,604 --> 00:05:44,996
Fred, I can't believe

106
00:05:44,996 --> 00:05:46,476
you took credit
for my plan again.

107
00:05:46,476 --> 00:05:47,825
Some plan.

108
00:05:47,825 --> 00:05:49,958
That ghost pawed me
for an hour and a half.

109
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:52,569
Daph, it's not our fault
you always get kidnapped.

110
00:05:52,569 --> 00:05:55,006
I do not always get kidnapped.

111
00:05:55,006 --> 00:05:56,573
Can't believe you'd say that.

112
00:05:56,573 --> 00:05:57,966
Oh, please.

113
00:05:57,966 --> 00:05:59,968
You come with
your own ransom note.

114
00:06:01,622 --> 00:06:03,014
Hey, my glasses!

115
00:06:03,014 --> 00:06:05,365
Who's helpless now?

116
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:07,149
I'm going
to kill you, Daphne!

117
00:06:07,149 --> 00:06:08,803
Whoa! Whoa!
Watch the ascot!

118
00:06:08,803 --> 00:06:10,370
Hey, you guys, look,

119
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:14,243
I know I'm just the dude
that carries the bags,

120
00:06:14,243 --> 00:06:17,333
but it seems to me we all play
an important part in this group.

121
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:20,162
I mean,
we're just like

122
00:06:20,162 --> 00:06:21,468
a big, delicious banana split.

123
00:06:21,468 --> 00:06:24,122
Fred, you're the big banana.

124
00:06:24,122 --> 00:06:27,604
Daphne's the pastrami
and gum-flavored ice cream.

125
00:06:27,604 --> 00:06:29,389
And Velma,

126
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:31,739
you're
the sweet-and-sour mustard sauce

127
00:06:31,739 --> 00:06:32,740
that goes on top.

128
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:34,568
Mm-mm!

129
00:06:34,568 --> 00:06:35,699
That sounds pretty good,
doesn't it?

130
00:06:37,005 --> 00:06:38,528
You know what, Shaggy?

131
00:06:38,528 --> 00:06:40,617
You've really
put it in perspective for me.

132
00:06:41,836 --> 00:06:43,315
Thanks.

133
00:06:44,752 --> 00:06:45,709
I quit.

134
00:06:46,928 --> 00:06:48,146
No.

135
00:06:48,146 --> 00:06:50,105
No way.

136
00:06:50,105 --> 00:06:53,717
You can't quit.

137
00:06:53,717 --> 00:06:55,545
I was going to quit
in, like, two seconds.

138
00:06:55,545 --> 00:06:58,374
Now everyone will think
I copied off the smart girl.

139
00:06:58,374 --> 00:07:00,158
Now, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

140
00:07:02,726 --> 00:07:03,814
Maybe I quit.

141
00:07:06,295 --> 00:07:07,296
I do.

142
00:07:08,689 --> 00:07:09,690
Yeah, I quit.

143
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:12,083
I'm out of here.

144
00:07:14,956 --> 00:07:16,044
Good riddance.

145
00:07:16,044 --> 00:07:17,045
Don't--

146
00:07:17,045 --> 00:07:18,307
No. Don't go.

147
00:07:18,307 --> 00:07:20,962
Come on, you guys,
don't do this.

148
00:07:20,962 --> 00:07:24,139
Please don't go.

149
00:07:24,139 --> 00:07:27,185
[WHIMPERS]

150
00:07:27,185 --> 00:07:28,839
Do I quit?

151
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:31,799
No, Scoob...

152
00:07:31,799 --> 00:07:33,931
friends don't quit.

153
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:40,372
It looks like
it's you and me for a while.

154
00:07:40,372 --> 00:07:42,418
What now, Shaggy?

155
00:07:42,418 --> 00:07:45,943
I guess we'll all just do
what we do best, Scoob.

156
00:07:46,988 --> 00:07:50,470
[ REGGAE MUSIC PLAYING ]

157
00:07:55,562 --> 00:07:58,347
SHAGGY: This is primo.

158
00:07:58,347 --> 00:08:02,743
Man, talk about toasted.

159
00:08:02,743 --> 00:08:04,571
Man, the only thing
I like better

160
00:08:04,571 --> 00:08:06,921
than an eggplant burger

161
00:08:06,921 --> 00:08:10,446
is a chocolate-covered
eggplant burger.

162
00:08:10,446 --> 00:08:12,404
With hot sauce.
Ra-cha-cha-cha!

163
00:08:12,404 --> 00:08:14,929
Hee-hee-hee!

164
00:08:14,929 --> 00:08:18,933
Yeah, just another beautiful day
in paradise.

165
00:08:18,933 --> 00:08:20,587
[BANGING]

166
00:08:20,587 --> 00:08:23,894
I'm looking for a "Mr. Rogers"
and a "Mr. Doo."

167
00:08:23,894 --> 00:08:24,939
The detectives?

168
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:26,462
It's probably just somebody

169
00:08:26,462 --> 00:08:28,159
looking for us to solve
some terrifying mystery.

170
00:08:28,159 --> 00:08:29,596
Nobody home!

171
00:08:29,596 --> 00:08:32,512
Quick, Scoob-o, grab the food-o.
Let's scram-o.

172
00:08:34,122 --> 00:08:37,429
I'm looking for a "Mr. Rogers"
and a "Mr. Doo."

173
00:08:39,562 --> 00:08:40,520
Let's go!

174
00:08:43,784 --> 00:08:45,176
I'm sorry, dude.

175
00:08:45,176 --> 00:08:47,483
Look, uh...
I'd love to help you out.

176
00:08:47,483 --> 00:08:49,441
You look like
a really nice guy.

177
00:08:49,441 --> 00:08:51,705
We're not detectives anymore.

178
00:08:51,705 --> 00:08:53,968
I've been sent
by Mr. Emile Mondavarious

179
00:08:53,968 --> 00:08:55,491
to invite you

180
00:08:55,491 --> 00:08:57,928
to his world-famous
amusement park, Spooky Island.

181
00:08:57,928 --> 00:08:59,582
We don't go near places

182
00:08:59,582 --> 00:09:01,410
with "spooky," "haunted,"
"forbidden," or "creepy"

183
00:09:01,410 --> 00:09:02,411
in the name.

184
00:09:02,411 --> 00:09:04,152
Or "hydrocolonic".

185
00:09:04,152 --> 00:09:06,894
Right, but that's
for a different reason, man.

186
00:09:06,894 --> 00:09:10,114
But he'd like you
to solve a mystery.

187
00:09:10,114 --> 00:09:12,769
He'll pay you a fee of $10,000.

188
00:09:12,769 --> 00:09:14,292
It's just,

189
00:09:14,292 --> 00:09:16,599
materialism's
not really our bag, man.

190
00:09:16,599 --> 00:09:17,818
Free airfare.

191
00:09:17,818 --> 00:09:18,906
No, thanks.

192
00:09:18,906 --> 00:09:20,342
Room and board.
No, thanks.

193
00:09:20,342 --> 00:09:22,387
And all you can eat.

194
00:09:25,216 --> 00:09:26,914
All you can eat?

195
00:09:42,146 --> 00:09:43,191
Fred?

196
00:09:43,191 --> 00:09:44,235
Velma?

197
00:09:44,235 --> 00:09:48,022
Are you going this way?

198
00:09:48,022 --> 00:09:48,979
Mm-hmm.

199
00:09:52,461 --> 00:09:53,462
How have you...

200
00:09:53,462 --> 00:09:54,550
Been?

201
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,160
Yes.

202
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,597
Great. Great.

203
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:58,946
I'm on
the lecture circuit

204
00:09:58,946 --> 00:10:00,469
with my new book...

205
00:10:00,469 --> 00:10:03,603
Fred on Fred:

The Many Faces of Me.

206
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,474
Jinkies, that's impressive.

207
00:10:05,474 --> 00:10:07,824
And yourself?

208
00:10:07,824 --> 00:10:10,000
I've been working at NASA,

209
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,915
developing hydropowered
missile defense systems.

210
00:10:11,915 --> 00:10:14,004
But, more importantly,

211
00:10:14,004 --> 00:10:16,093
I'm on a journey
of self-discovery.

212
00:10:16,093 --> 00:10:18,095
NASA?

213
00:10:18,095 --> 00:10:19,488
ANNOUNCER:
Charter service

to Spooky Island

214
00:10:19,488 --> 00:10:21,229
will begin boarding

momentarily.

215
00:10:21,229 --> 00:10:23,013
What do you mean

216
00:10:23,013 --> 00:10:24,362
I can't have
seven carry-on bags?

217
00:10:24,362 --> 00:10:25,407
That's so economy.

218
00:10:25,407 --> 00:10:26,408
Crap.Crap.

219
00:10:28,497 --> 00:10:30,064
Oh, no.

220
00:10:30,064 --> 00:10:32,806
I'm not talking to you guys.

221
00:10:37,419 --> 00:10:38,899
What are you doing here?

222
00:10:38,899 --> 00:10:40,204
Isn't it obvious?

223
00:10:40,204 --> 00:10:41,989
We all received
the same letter

224
00:10:41,989 --> 00:10:43,555
from one Emile Mondavarious,

225
00:10:43,555 --> 00:10:45,645
the reclusive owner
of Spooky Island.

226
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:47,603
It's not fair.

227
00:10:47,603 --> 00:10:50,171
I was going to
solve the mystery all by myself.

228
00:10:50,171 --> 00:10:51,476
And when you get caught?

229
00:10:51,476 --> 00:10:53,130
I'm a black belt now.

230
00:10:53,130 --> 00:10:56,612
I've transformed my body
into a dangerous weapon.

231
00:10:58,832 --> 00:10:59,963
It's true.

232
00:10:59,963 --> 00:11:02,183
Far out.

233
00:11:02,183 --> 00:11:04,533
I guess we're, like,
all going to Spooky Island, man.

234
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:06,187
Where's Scooby?

235
00:11:13,585 --> 00:11:14,935
Hello.

236
00:11:17,459 --> 00:11:19,983
They don't allow big dogs
on the plane.

237
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:26,120
You've got to be kidding.

238
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,470
No one is stupid enough
to believe that.

239
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:30,690
Who's the ugly old broad?

240
00:11:33,388 --> 00:11:35,738
Say hello to Grandma.

241
00:11:35,738 --> 00:11:37,218
SCOOBY-DOO: Aloha.

242
00:11:37,218 --> 00:11:39,481
Flight 3774 to Spooky Island
now boarding.

243
00:11:39,481 --> 00:11:41,701
I wouldn't have agreed to come
if I knew.

244
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:45,008
Wait, just think about it
for one minute.

245
00:11:45,008 --> 00:11:46,618
Mystery Inc. reunites.

246
00:11:46,618 --> 00:11:49,709
We'll be a team again,
just like the old days,

247
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,667
so come on, gang,

248
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:53,974
let's do that thing
where we all put our hands in,

249
00:11:53,974 --> 00:11:56,628
we lift them up,
and we go "Whoo-hoo-hoo!"

250
00:11:56,628 --> 00:11:59,414
Only if Fred and Velma do it.

251
00:12:02,983 --> 00:12:05,028
People are watching, Shag.

252
00:12:13,428 --> 00:12:15,386
Roo-hoo.

253
00:12:15,386 --> 00:12:17,475
Yeah, Scoob, "Roo-hoo."

254
00:12:17,475 --> 00:12:18,955
Come on, buddy.

255
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:42,413
Now, that is
a beautiful work of art.

256
00:12:42,413 --> 00:12:44,502
Ra-ha.

257
00:13:00,954 --> 00:13:04,479
Would you mind me
taking a seat there next to...

258
00:13:04,479 --> 00:13:06,437
To my grandma.
That's my grandma.

259
00:13:06,437 --> 00:13:07,961
Hi, Grandma.

260
00:13:07,961 --> 00:13:09,092
Like, no.

261
00:13:12,313 --> 00:13:13,444
Thanks.

262
00:13:13,444 --> 00:13:14,924
You're welcome.

263
00:13:16,621 --> 00:13:18,101
Bless you.

264
00:13:18,101 --> 00:13:21,975
I'm sorry. My allergies.

265
00:13:21,975 --> 00:13:23,933
It's usually only dogs
that do it.

266
00:13:27,763 --> 00:13:29,634
Maybe I'd better move.

267
00:13:29,634 --> 00:13:30,766
No, wait.

268
00:13:32,072 --> 00:13:34,770
It's probably
just my grandma's perfume.

269
00:13:34,770 --> 00:13:38,078
Yeah, even I sometimes get
a little allergic, you know.

270
00:13:38,078 --> 00:13:40,167
Oh, jeez.

271
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:42,952
'Cause I'm pretty sure

