00:13:42,952 --> 00:13:44,998
Grandma wants to go back
and visit with her pal Velma.

273
00:13:44,998 --> 00:13:47,609
Right, Grandma?

274
00:13:47,609 --> 00:13:49,480
Okay.

275
00:13:54,877 --> 00:13:57,532
Boy, oh, boy,

276
00:13:57,532 --> 00:13:58,794
those sure do look
like Scooby Snacks.

277
00:13:58,794 --> 00:14:01,231
I know they're for dogs,

278
00:14:01,231 --> 00:14:04,539
but they're 100% vegetarian,
and I love them.

279
00:14:04,539 --> 00:14:05,932
Like, me too.

280
00:14:05,932 --> 00:14:07,672
Far out.

281
00:14:07,672 --> 00:14:09,936
I've never met another person
who loves Scooby Snacks.

282
00:14:09,936 --> 00:14:10,937
Me neither.

283
00:14:10,937 --> 00:14:12,329
I'm Mary Jane.

284
00:14:12,329 --> 00:14:14,375
Like, that's my favorite name.

285
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:15,419
Really?

286
00:14:15,419 --> 00:14:16,464
Yeah.

287
00:14:16,464 --> 00:14:17,465
No way.

288
00:14:23,819 --> 00:14:24,864
Hello.

289
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,268
Grandma?

290
00:14:38,268 --> 00:14:40,488
Velma, it's simple
behavior modification.

291
00:14:40,488 --> 00:14:41,619
To cause a dog

292
00:14:41,619 --> 00:14:43,273
to discontinue
any action,

293
00:14:43,273 --> 00:14:44,971
flick it on the nose.

294
00:14:44,971 --> 00:14:46,363
Observe.

295
00:14:46,363 --> 00:14:47,930
Scoob?

296
00:14:49,976 --> 00:14:51,455
See?

297
00:14:56,765 --> 00:14:59,159
SHAGGY:
Sit, Grandma! Bad Grandma!

298
00:14:59,159 --> 00:15:01,901
Don't eat the kitty!

299
00:15:08,255 --> 00:15:10,866
ANNOUNCER:

Welcome to Spooky Island...

300
00:15:10,866 --> 00:15:12,694
the frightfully popular

301
00:15:12,694 --> 00:15:16,045
spring break spot

for college students.

302
00:15:16,045 --> 00:15:18,395
Catch our

Electrical Torture Parade,

303
00:15:18,395 --> 00:15:20,397
"It's a Dead World After All"

304
00:15:20,397 --> 00:15:24,401
and the world-famous

"Splatterhorn".

305
00:15:24,401 --> 00:15:27,491
Scooby-Doo!

306
00:15:27,491 --> 00:15:29,276
And the rest of Mystery Inc.

307
00:15:29,276 --> 00:15:30,842
It's marvelous to see you!

308
00:15:30,842 --> 00:15:32,540
How fanta--

309
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:34,542
That's the second time

this week.

310
00:15:35,978 --> 00:15:37,153
Thank goodness.

311
00:15:37,153 --> 00:15:39,547
Sorry, it's a new toy.

312
00:15:39,547 --> 00:15:41,810
I'm just getting up to speed
with it.

313
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:43,551
Welcome.

314
00:15:43,551 --> 00:15:44,682
Thank goodness.

315
00:15:44,682 --> 00:15:46,510
I was afraid
I'd have to lug those

316
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:47,903
all the way to the hotel.

317
00:15:47,903 --> 00:15:50,036
That's what
Spooky Island's about,

318
00:15:50,036 --> 00:15:52,299
realizing your worst fears.

319
00:15:52,299 --> 00:15:54,083
I'm Emile Mondavarious,

320
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:57,434
the owner
of this amusement park.

321
00:15:57,434 --> 00:15:59,088
VELMA:
You seem less...

322
00:15:59,088 --> 00:16:00,350
Spooky.

323
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:01,699
Than we'd have guessed.

324
00:16:01,699 --> 00:16:04,876
I can be pretty spooky
when called upon.

325
00:16:04,876 --> 00:16:05,877
I can go...

326
00:16:05,877 --> 00:16:08,663
"Rrrowr, rrowr!"

327
00:16:08,663 --> 00:16:11,753
Claws and everything.

328
00:16:11,753 --> 00:16:14,364
You wouldn't want to run into me
in a dark alley.

329
00:16:14,364 --> 00:16:16,714
So you're the one
who brought us here?

330
00:16:16,714 --> 00:16:18,586
No.

331
00:16:18,586 --> 00:16:22,068
What brought you here
was your insatiable appetite

332
00:16:22,068 --> 00:16:23,591
for a juicy mystery.

333
00:16:23,591 --> 00:16:28,161
The truth is,
Mystery Inc. is broken up.

334
00:16:28,161 --> 00:16:30,598
That's the beauty
of broken things.

335
00:16:30,598 --> 00:16:31,903
It can be fixed.

336
00:16:31,903 --> 00:16:34,036
Therein lies
its potential.

337
00:16:34,036 --> 00:16:36,386
And I need you
to fix Spooky Island.

338
00:16:36,386 --> 00:16:37,953
VELMA: What's the problem?

339
00:16:37,953 --> 00:16:39,476
EMILE: I believe

340
00:16:39,476 --> 00:16:41,652
somebody's casting a spell
on the students.

341
00:16:41,652 --> 00:16:44,307
Now, listen and look around.

342
00:16:44,307 --> 00:16:46,614
Notice any difference

343
00:16:46,614 --> 00:16:49,095
between those arriving
and those departing?

344
00:16:49,095 --> 00:16:53,012
DAPHNE:They look like sober,
well-behaved college kids.

345
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,057
EMILE: Precisely.
They didn't before they came.

346
00:16:55,057 --> 00:16:56,798
They've changed.

347
00:16:56,798 --> 00:17:00,323
In other words, a magic spell.

348
00:17:00,323 --> 00:17:02,456
Carol!
Carol, how was the island?

349
00:17:02,456 --> 00:17:04,762
Are you tricking on me?

350
00:17:06,808 --> 00:17:09,419
It's me, Brad.

351
00:17:09,419 --> 00:17:11,334
We've known each other
since we were 3.

352
00:17:11,334 --> 00:17:13,075
Back off my grill, son!

353
00:17:13,075 --> 00:17:15,469
Carol,
what are you doing?

354
00:17:26,871 --> 00:17:28,569
I'm terrified.

355
00:17:28,569 --> 00:17:31,311
The young people
that come off that barge,

356
00:17:31,311 --> 00:17:33,965
the people I love the most,

357
00:17:33,965 --> 00:17:35,750
they're in danger.

358
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:38,057
I'm going
to solve this one first.

359
00:17:39,101 --> 00:17:40,233
Not before I solve it first.

360
00:17:40,233 --> 00:17:42,539
You'll look like total idiots

361
00:17:42,539 --> 00:17:44,889
when you're captured
and I save you.

362
00:17:44,889 --> 00:17:47,936
Thank you. Marvelous.

363
00:17:47,936 --> 00:17:49,503
Maybe we can celebrate later

364
00:17:49,503 --> 00:17:50,591
by having
a little spookapalooza.

365
00:17:50,591 --> 00:17:54,464
Spookapalooza? Ruh-oh.

366
00:17:57,337 --> 00:17:59,426
So you haven't noticed
anything unusual

367
00:17:59,426 --> 00:18:01,384
since you started working here?

368
00:18:01,384 --> 00:18:04,213
Any weirdos
running around?

369
00:18:04,213 --> 00:18:05,910
Uh...no.

370
00:18:12,352 --> 00:18:15,616
[ CHANTING ]

371
00:18:25,495 --> 00:18:28,194
Welcome, dear victims.

372
00:18:28,194 --> 00:18:32,676
My name is N'Goo Tauna.

373
00:18:32,676 --> 00:18:36,941
This is
my evil best pal, Zarkos.

374
00:18:36,941 --> 00:18:40,162
You may recognize him
from
Telemundo

375
00:18:40,162 --> 00:18:41,990
as the famous masked wrestler...

376
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:44,123
Zarkos.

377
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:46,647
This enchanted island

378
00:18:46,647 --> 00:18:51,086
is a thoroughfare
to the supernatural realm.

379
00:18:51,086 --> 00:18:52,783
For centuries,

380
00:18:52,783 --> 00:18:54,481
it was home to creatures

381
00:18:54,481 --> 00:18:57,962
who lived on the island,
undisturbed.

382
00:18:59,921 --> 00:19:02,880
But then, 10 years ago,

383
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:06,754
Emile Mondavarious

384
00:19:06,754 --> 00:19:14,065
antagonized these ancient beings
by building a theme park here.

385
00:19:16,459 --> 00:19:20,376
The creatures are furious,
my friends,

386
00:19:20,376 --> 00:19:22,683
and I assure you

387
00:19:22,683 --> 00:19:25,425
while you party...

388
00:19:25,425 --> 00:19:30,908
they plot their revenge!

389
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:40,222
Do my friends
frighten you?

390
00:19:42,572 --> 00:19:44,661
They would,

391
00:19:44,661 --> 00:19:48,404
if it weren't for
the holographic projectors

392
00:19:48,404 --> 00:19:50,754
there, and there,

393
00:19:50,754 --> 00:19:53,148
and there.

394
00:19:53,148 --> 00:19:55,803
What a smart
little one.

395
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,815
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

396
00:20:07,815 --> 00:20:10,600
Hello.
Dead Mike's.

397
00:20:13,429 --> 00:20:15,823
We got a "Mr. Doo" here?

398
00:20:15,823 --> 00:20:18,347
I got a call for a "Mr. Doo."

399
00:20:18,347 --> 00:20:20,001
Melvin Doo?

400
00:20:20,001 --> 00:20:22,569
No. Scooby.

401
00:20:25,311 --> 00:20:26,660
Hello?

402
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:31,665
MAN:
Got a bag

of hamburgers for you.

403
00:20:31,665 --> 00:20:34,842
Just walk into the dark,

shadowy part of the forest

404
00:20:34,842 --> 00:20:37,975
where no one

can see you.

405
00:20:37,975 --> 00:20:39,281
Okay.

406
00:20:43,894 --> 00:20:46,245
SHAGGY: Want a stuffed thingy?

407
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:47,376
Nobody can win those.

408
00:20:47,376 --> 00:20:49,030
Fred says
it's a worthless talent,

409
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:51,641
that I should've
learned French instead.

410
00:20:51,641 --> 00:20:53,556
I say you don't
need to know

411
00:20:53,556 --> 00:20:55,384
what
"Voulez-vous

coucher avec moi"
means

412
00:20:55,384 --> 00:20:58,518
to love that song.

413
00:20:58,518 --> 00:21:00,607
I think being good
at crane machine

414
00:21:00,607 --> 00:21:02,522
is way cooler
than French.

415
00:21:03,827 --> 00:21:05,873
Voilà!

416
00:21:05,873 --> 00:21:08,354
Nobody's ever given me

417
00:21:08,354 --> 00:21:11,226
a stuffed dismembered head
before.

418
00:21:37,861 --> 00:21:40,037
Excuse me.

419
00:21:41,909 --> 00:21:44,694
Now I have to start
my voodoo ritual all over again!

420
00:21:44,694 --> 00:21:46,087
Voodoo ritual?

421
00:21:46,087 --> 00:21:48,524
I was about to sacrifice
this chicken.

422
00:21:48,524 --> 00:21:50,613
That chicken's not alive.

423
00:21:50,613 --> 00:21:52,441
I know it's not alive,
little girl.

424
00:21:52,441 --> 00:21:54,617
Did you figure that out
when you didn't see its head?

425
00:21:54,617 --> 00:21:56,750
No.

426
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:58,752
Why you all up
in the voodoo ritual space?

427
00:21:58,752 --> 00:22:01,276
I'm looking for clues
as to who's behind

428
00:22:01,276 --> 00:22:03,757
the students'
strange behavior.

429
00:22:03,757 --> 00:22:05,454
Well, here's a clue:

430
00:22:05,454 --> 00:22:07,456
Purple is a fall color.

431
00:22:07,456 --> 00:22:08,762
It's the middle of May!

432
00:22:08,762 --> 00:22:11,242
Pardon?

433
00:22:11,242 --> 00:22:13,680
Get off this island.
Go home.

434
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:17,379
Go home before evil befalls
your skinny, aerobicized booty.

435
00:22:17,379 --> 00:22:19,425
And whatever you do,

436
00:22:19,425 --> 00:22:21,731
do not,

437
00:22:21,731 --> 00:22:25,909
I repeat, do not go into
that Spooky Island castle.

438
00:22:25,909 --> 00:22:27,520
Ah-hah!

439
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:29,609
You want me
to go to that castle.

440
00:22:29,609 --> 00:22:30,958
Didn't you hear what I said?

441
00:22:30,958 --> 00:22:32,829
But you're scary.

442
00:22:32,829 --> 00:22:34,875
You knew I'd do
the opposite of what you said.

443
00:22:34,875 --> 00:22:36,485
You told me
not to go to the castle

444
00:22:36,485 --> 00:22:38,052
so I would go to the castle,

445
00:22:38,052 --> 00:22:41,229
where you set a trap
to capture me...

446
00:22:41,229 --> 00:22:43,144
unless...

447
00:22:43,144 --> 00:22:45,015
you knew I'd figure it out,

448
00:22:45,015 --> 00:22:46,626
so you told me not to go

449
00:22:46,626 --> 00:22:48,628
so I'd think
you wanted me to go,

450
00:22:48,628 --> 00:22:50,325
so I wouldn't go.

451
00:22:50,325 --> 00:22:51,761
Huh?

452
00:22:51,761 --> 00:22:53,502
I'll find out what you're hiding
in that castle.

453
00:22:53,502 --> 00:22:55,112
You watch.

454
00:22:55,112 --> 00:22:59,465
What in the world?

455
00:22:59,465 --> 00:23:00,944
Hamburgers...

456
00:23:00,944 --> 00:23:03,556
where are you?

457
00:23:06,994 --> 00:23:08,125
Hamburgers. Oh, boy.

458
00:23:14,871 --> 00:23:17,352
Hamburgers.

459
00:23:17,352 --> 00:23:20,442
Thank you.

460
00:23:43,857 --> 00:23:45,467
Shaggy!

461
00:24:07,184 --> 00:24:08,664
It's been really nice.

462
00:24:08,664 --> 00:24:11,841
Shaggy!

463
00:24:12,886 --> 00:24:15,323
Monster! Monster!

464
00:24:15,323 --> 00:24:17,064
A monster?

465
00:24:22,722 --> 00:24:25,986
Scooby-Doo,
quit goofing around, man.

466
00:24:25,986 --> 00:24:27,204
I guess I should go.

467
00:24:31,339 --> 00:24:33,863
Bye, Scooby.

468
00:24:36,344 --> 00:24:37,345
Bless you.

469
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:44,657
Shaggy. Scooby.

470
00:24:51,315 --> 00:24:52,316
No way.

471
00:24:52,316 --> 00:24:54,014
Shaggy...

472
00:24:54,014 --> 00:24:55,494
Scoob and me
don't do castles.

473
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:57,887
Why not?

474
00:24:57,887 --> 00:25:00,194
They have paintings
with eyes that watch you

475
00:25:00,194 --> 00:25:01,935
and suits of armor
you think is a statue

476
00:25:01,935 --> 00:25:03,937
but there's a guy inside

477
00:25:03,937 --> 00:25:07,244
who follows you
every time you turn around.

478
00:25:07,244 --> 00:25:09,551
How many times did that happen?

479
00:25:09,551 --> 00:25:12,032
12. We're not going to do it.

480
00:25:12,032 --> 00:25:14,077
That's right.

481
00:25:14,077 --> 00:25:17,254
Scooby?

482
00:25:17,254 --> 00:25:19,735
Did you hurt
your paw?

483
00:25:19,735 --> 00:25:21,824
Would you do it
for a Scooby Snack?

484
00:25:21,824 --> 00:25:25,262
Oh, boy!

485
00:25:25,262 --> 00:25:26,829
And you'll be fearless?

486
00:25:26,829 --> 00:25:28,439
Fearless?

487
00:25:35,403 --> 00:25:37,448
Hong Kong Phooey,
watch the fists of fury.

488
00:25:37,448 --> 00:25:39,059
Here you go.

489
00:25:39,059 --> 00:25:41,104
Thank you.

490
00:25:41,104 --> 00:25:43,759
There's plenty more
where that came from.

491
00:25:43,759 --> 00:25:48,198
Let's go before someone sees.

492
00:25:48,198 --> 00:25:50,853
You're not going to
stay out here alone, are you?

493
00:25:50,853 --> 00:25:52,768
No thank you.

494
00:26:03,083 --> 00:26:04,040
Oh, boy.

495
00:26:07,696 --> 00:26:10,394
This place is, like,

uber
creepy.

496
00:26:10,394 --> 00:26:12,919
Yeah,
uber
creepy.

497
00:26:12,919 --> 00:26:15,138
The only thing missing
is a mindless zombie.

498
00:26:21,318 --> 00:26:22,972
Fred, get back.

499
00:26:22,972 --> 00:26:24,408
I found this place.

500
00:26:24,408 --> 00:26:25,801
I call dibs on its clues.

501
00:26:25,801 --> 00:26:27,847
I've already found some clues.

502
00:26:27,847 --> 00:26:29,239
What?

503
00:26:29,239 --> 00:26:31,981
I followed
some weird footprints here.

504
00:26:31,981 --> 00:26:33,417
It might be dangerous for you.

505
00:26:33,417 --> 00:26:35,158
If anyone messes with me,

506
00:26:35,158 --> 00:26:37,508
I'll open
a can of Chinese whoop-ass.

507
00:26:41,208 --> 00:26:42,470
Velma!

508
00:26:42,470 --> 00:26:44,298
What are you doing here?

509
00:26:44,298 --> 00:26:47,344
This ride was closed
for construction.

510
00:26:47,344 --> 00:26:49,608
It's the most likely place
to hatch a plan.

511
00:26:49,608 --> 00:26:53,002
And I wanted
to scare Daphne.

512
00:26:53,002 --> 00:26:54,438
Since we're all together,

513
00:26:54,438 --> 00:26:57,006
let's split up
and look for more clues.

514
00:26:57,006 --> 00:26:58,486
Daphne, you and I--

515
00:26:58,486 --> 00:26:59,922
Typical.

516
00:26:59,922 --> 00:27:01,054
What?

517
00:27:01,054 --> 00:27:02,925
Oh, nothing.

518
00:27:02,925 --> 00:27:06,059
I was always picked last
for the teams.

519
00:27:06,059 --> 00:27:07,277
Okay.

520
00:27:07,277 --> 00:27:08,975
Daphne,
exit through the entrance.

521
00:27:08,975 --> 00:27:12,631
Velma and I
will enter through the exit.

522
00:27:12,631 --> 00:27:14,763
And Shaggy and Scooby...

523
00:27:14,763 --> 00:27:18,854
do whatever you guys do.

524
00:27:31,737 --> 00:27:33,869
Wow...

525
00:27:35,262 --> 00:27:37,481
Look at this, huh, Scoob?

526
00:27:37,481 --> 00:27:40,006
It's like a medieval
Sizzler.

527
00:27:40,006 --> 00:27:42,443
Pinch me, I'm in heaven--

528
00:27:42,443 --> 00:27:44,140
Ow. It's an expression, Scoob.

529
00:27:44,140 --> 00:27:45,664
Sorry.

530
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:06,119
Velma, I never meant to--
Well, you know,

531
00:28:06,119 --> 00:28:07,773
pick you last.

532
00:28:07,773 --> 00:28:09,078
Don't worry about it, Fred.

533
00:28:09,078 --> 00:28:10,776
I know you.

534
00:28:10,776 --> 00:28:13,430
All you care about
are swimsuit models.

535
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:14,693
No!

536
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:16,695
Look, I'm a man
of substance.

537
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:19,306
Dorky chicks like you
turn me on too.

538
00:28:24,224 --> 00:28:26,182
That's a compliment.

539
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:55,995
Yes! Yes!

