00:28:55,995 --> 00:28:57,866
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

541
00:28:57,866 --> 00:29:01,174
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah. Oh, no!

542
00:29:04,177 --> 00:29:06,309
CREEPY VOICE:

And now for our dinner show.

543
00:29:14,361 --> 00:29:15,362
Watch out!

544
00:29:20,933 --> 00:29:22,586
I've got
a bad feeling about this.

545
00:29:22,586 --> 00:29:24,066
Me too.

546
00:29:24,066 --> 00:29:26,590
And now for the main course...

547
00:29:26,590 --> 00:29:28,636
you!

548
00:29:28,636 --> 00:29:30,420
[EVIL LAUGHTER]

549
00:29:30,420 --> 00:29:32,509
Feast on this.

550
00:29:41,692 --> 00:29:43,651
Jinkies.

551
00:29:43,651 --> 00:29:46,045
They're moving
toward us.

552
00:29:46,045 --> 00:29:48,612
Run!

553
00:29:48,612 --> 00:29:49,657
We're trapped.

554
00:29:49,657 --> 00:29:51,746
Quick, try the bookcase.

555
00:29:51,746 --> 00:29:54,270
One of these
has to open a secret passageway.

556
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:55,619
Velma, this is a ride.

557
00:29:55,619 --> 00:29:57,534
You got a better plan, Fred?

558
00:30:02,931 --> 00:30:04,454
What do we do?

559
00:30:04,454 --> 00:30:06,979
Do what we do best, Scoob--

560
00:30:06,979 --> 00:30:08,850
eat.

561
00:30:10,983 --> 00:30:12,462
It's plastic.

562
00:30:12,462 --> 00:30:15,074
So what?
You drink out of a toilet.

563
00:30:15,074 --> 00:30:18,642
So do you.

564
00:30:18,642 --> 00:30:20,862
I'm not helpless.
I'm not helpless.

565
00:30:20,862 --> 00:30:23,430
I am helpless.
I'm going to die!

566
00:30:43,276 --> 00:30:46,801
We made it, Scoob. We're alive!

567
00:30:51,980 --> 00:30:53,112
That was weird.

568
00:30:53,112 --> 00:30:54,504
Fred?

569
00:30:54,504 --> 00:30:56,985
Freddy?

570
00:30:56,985 --> 00:30:59,074
Are you all right?

571
00:31:10,781 --> 00:31:12,914
The last book.

572
00:31:16,570 --> 00:31:18,267
I don't feel so good.

573
00:31:18,267 --> 00:31:19,703
Reminds me of the time

574
00:31:19,703 --> 00:31:22,010
we tried to eat
that guy in the hot-dog costume.

575
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:25,492
Looks like
some kind of school.

576
00:31:25,492 --> 00:31:27,450
In a spooky
castle ride?

577
00:31:27,450 --> 00:31:28,582
Fishy.

578
00:31:51,126 --> 00:31:53,824
Welcome to America.

579
00:31:53,824 --> 00:31:56,044
I am using the language

English.

580
00:31:56,044 --> 00:31:57,524
Shaggy, look.

581
00:31:57,524 --> 00:31:58,699
Let's check it out.

582
00:32:04,357 --> 00:32:05,880
Oh, boy.

583
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:08,709
Lights, camera, action,
huh, Scoob?

584
00:32:08,709 --> 00:32:11,190
Now that you're a young adult,

585
00:32:11,190 --> 00:32:14,715
you'll need to learn

societal do's...

586
00:32:14,715 --> 00:32:16,499
and don'ts.

587
00:32:16,499 --> 00:32:18,371
Interaction

between young people

588
00:32:18,371 --> 00:32:21,504
is polite and casual.

589
00:32:25,552 --> 00:32:27,032
Hey, sorry, bro.

590
00:32:27,032 --> 00:32:30,165
I will crush your bones

into dust.

591
00:32:33,908 --> 00:32:37,085
Let's see how the situation

should be handled.

592
00:32:37,085 --> 00:32:41,568
Remember, today's young people

have a language all their own.

593
00:32:45,354 --> 00:32:47,052
Sorry, bro.

594
00:32:47,052 --> 00:32:50,272
No big whoop, dog.

Catch that new vid on the box?

595
00:32:50,272 --> 00:32:51,795
True dat.

596
00:32:51,795 --> 00:32:53,536
I'm up to sniznuff

on all popular trends.

597
00:32:53,536 --> 00:32:56,496
Word.

598
00:32:56,496 --> 00:32:58,063
It seems to be

599
00:32:58,063 --> 00:33:00,065
a brainwashing facility
of some type.

600
00:33:00,065 --> 00:33:02,719
Wherever
there's a brainwashing cult,

601
00:33:02,719 --> 00:33:05,461
there's always
a power-hungry leader.

602
00:33:05,461 --> 00:33:06,767
The Papa Smurf figure.

603
00:33:06,767 --> 00:33:08,029
Mondavarious.

604
00:33:08,029 --> 00:33:09,422
Mm...

605
00:33:09,422 --> 00:33:11,250
Then why would he have
invited us here?

606
00:34:00,212 --> 00:34:01,865
Jellybeans.

607
00:34:01,865 --> 00:34:03,432
[BELCHES]

608
00:34:05,869 --> 00:34:07,349
I'll have whatever he's having.

609
00:34:07,349 --> 00:34:09,525
[BELCHES]

610
00:34:09,525 --> 00:34:11,788
[BELCHES]

611
00:34:13,790 --> 00:34:16,576
Are you challenging me?

612
00:34:16,576 --> 00:34:19,448
Maybe.

613
00:34:20,884 --> 00:34:22,973
[BELCHES]

614
00:34:25,237 --> 00:34:29,067
[BREAKS WIND]

615
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:30,677
Pull my finger.

616
00:34:30,677 --> 00:34:32,940
Uh-uh. Too late.

617
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:34,463
[BELCHES]

618
00:34:38,511 --> 00:34:39,599
You're in trouble.

619
00:34:39,599 --> 00:34:41,209
Oh, boy.

620
00:34:41,209 --> 00:34:42,863
[BREAKS WIND]

621
00:34:47,563 --> 00:34:50,871
[SHAGGY AND SCOOBY-DOO
BREAKING WIND]

622
00:34:53,787 --> 00:34:57,834
I'm not stopping
till your fur's singed off.

623
00:35:07,017 --> 00:35:10,369
We're here to solve a mystery.

624
00:35:10,369 --> 00:35:11,326
Yeah, Scoob.

625
00:35:15,504 --> 00:35:17,463
[ALARM SOUNDING]

626
00:35:17,463 --> 00:35:19,334
Let's get out of here.

627
00:35:20,509 --> 00:35:22,207
Zoinks! Skedaddle!

628
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:32,565
I found
a neat and scary clue.

629
00:35:32,565 --> 00:35:34,132
Us too.

630
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:35,959
This is a brainwashing facility
for an evil cult.

631
00:35:35,959 --> 00:35:37,222
Maybe this is

632
00:35:37,222 --> 00:35:39,311
the secret relic thingy
they worship.

633
00:35:39,311 --> 00:35:42,966
We'll all be relics
if we don't get out of here.

634
00:35:42,966 --> 00:35:44,446
I've got a plan.

635
00:35:46,187 --> 00:35:48,450
What's that smell?

636
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:55,196
Sir, they found
the Daemon Ritus.

637
00:35:56,893 --> 00:35:58,591
They better not have gone far.

638
00:35:58,591 --> 00:35:59,722
[CRASHING]

639
00:36:01,594 --> 00:36:04,205
It is time
to summon the big muchachos.

640
00:36:05,424 --> 00:36:07,904
SHAGGY:
Like, oh, no!

641
00:36:07,904 --> 00:36:09,254
[BREAKING WIND]

642
00:36:33,713 --> 00:36:35,280
Ah, Mystery Inc.

643
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:38,544
You all seem rather cheery.
Good news, I hope?

644
00:36:38,544 --> 00:36:40,372
Mr. Mononucleosis....

645
00:36:40,372 --> 00:36:42,722
Yes?

646
00:36:42,722 --> 00:36:44,941
We have hit a clue smorgasbord.

647
00:36:46,116 --> 00:36:47,814
We have three suspects

648
00:36:47,814 --> 00:36:49,294
as to who's behind
this evil hooty.

649
00:36:49,294 --> 00:36:50,730
N'Goo Tauna.

650
00:36:50,730 --> 00:36:53,820
He believes
your park's on enchanted ground.

651
00:36:53,820 --> 00:36:55,169
DAPHNE: The voodoo man,

652
00:36:55,169 --> 00:36:57,389
who tricked me
into going to the castle.

653
00:36:57,389 --> 00:36:58,564
And you.

654
00:36:58,564 --> 00:37:00,000
Me?

655
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,176
FRED: Let's split up.

656
00:37:02,176 --> 00:37:03,612
I'll interview employees

657
00:37:03,612 --> 00:37:05,527
to see if they've noticed
anything odd.

658
00:37:05,527 --> 00:37:06,963
I'll translate

659
00:37:06,963 --> 00:37:09,227
these inscriptions
Daphne found.

660
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:11,403
I'll go research cults
on the Net.

661
00:37:14,797 --> 00:37:16,495
I'm a suspect?

662
00:37:16,495 --> 00:37:18,540
Don't take it personally.

663
00:37:18,540 --> 00:37:20,325
It's because you creep me out.

664
00:37:20,325 --> 00:37:22,588
I see.

665
00:37:22,588 --> 00:37:24,764
Fine.

666
00:37:42,825 --> 00:37:44,740
Jinkies.

667
00:38:00,408 --> 00:38:01,801
[PLAYING PIANO]

668
00:38:04,586 --> 00:38:08,198
Hey. Your friends
ditch you?

669
00:38:08,198 --> 00:38:10,200
No, I always did
the brainwork.

670
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:12,681
What's this?

671
00:38:12,681 --> 00:38:16,337
I believe it's called
the Daemon Ritus.

672
00:38:16,337 --> 00:38:19,209
Daemon Ritus?
What's it for?

673
00:38:19,209 --> 00:38:22,648
This describes
an old race of creatures.

674
00:38:22,648 --> 00:38:25,738
It's reminiscent
of Pandaemonous texts,

675
00:38:25,738 --> 00:38:27,435
so I can make some of it out.

676
00:38:27,435 --> 00:38:32,353
It looks like instructions
to some sort of secret ritual.

677
00:38:32,353 --> 00:38:33,789
It is fascinating.

678
00:38:33,789 --> 00:38:34,964
WAITER:
On the house.

679
00:38:34,964 --> 00:38:36,444
Nice sweater.

680
00:38:36,444 --> 00:38:37,489
You really dig
doing this, huh?

681
00:38:37,489 --> 00:38:40,492
Like, clues and stuff.

682
00:38:40,492 --> 00:38:42,624
Certainly.

683
00:38:42,624 --> 00:38:45,932
Really focusing on a mystery
reminds me of the old days.

684
00:38:48,630 --> 00:38:50,632
We were quite a crew back then.

685
00:38:52,112 --> 00:38:54,157
That was
the best time of my life.

686
00:38:54,157 --> 00:38:58,510
Shaggy and Scooby.
What goofballs!

687
00:38:58,510 --> 00:39:02,209
Kind of like they are today.

688
00:39:02,209 --> 00:39:03,950
And Daphne....

689
00:39:03,950 --> 00:39:06,126
So beautiful.

690
00:39:06,126 --> 00:39:08,781
She was the coolest girl
at Coolsville High.

691
00:39:08,781 --> 00:39:12,306
Fred. He was so handsome.

692
00:39:12,306 --> 00:39:14,352
And he really knew
how to accessorize.

693
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,441
Sounds perfect.

694
00:39:16,441 --> 00:39:19,748
Yeah, but every family
has one nut.

695
00:39:19,748 --> 00:39:22,272
Scrappy-Dappy-Doo!

696
00:39:22,272 --> 00:39:24,884
Ghosts don't stand a chance
with me.

697
00:39:24,884 --> 00:39:28,278
Let me at 'em.
I'll rock 'em. I'll sock 'em.

698
00:39:28,278 --> 00:39:31,760
For the 1000th time,
there's no such thing as ghosts.

699
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:32,979
Sure there are.

700
00:39:32,979 --> 00:39:34,415
When I find them,

701
00:39:34,415 --> 00:39:38,463
I'll give them a dose
of puppy power!

702
00:39:38,463 --> 00:39:42,075
Oh, God. He's peeing on me.

703
00:39:42,075 --> 00:39:44,599
[BRAKES SCREECHING]

704
00:39:48,081 --> 00:39:50,953
VELMA:
That little egomaniac

had flipped his lid.

705
00:39:50,953 --> 00:39:54,087
Scrappy, I told you,
no urinating on Daphne.

706
00:39:54,087 --> 00:39:55,697
It was an accident.

707
00:39:55,697 --> 00:39:57,133
You were marking
your territory.

708
00:39:57,133 --> 00:39:59,309
You don't have the scrote
for this job.

709
00:39:59,309 --> 00:40:01,224
Listen up, losers.

710
00:40:01,224 --> 00:40:05,751
The time has come to appoint me
your unquestioned leader.

711
00:40:05,751 --> 00:40:08,710
Either that, or I'm out of here.

712
00:40:11,931 --> 00:40:14,673
What's the idea?
You can't do this to me.

713
00:40:14,673 --> 00:40:16,501
People adore me.

714
00:40:16,501 --> 00:40:18,546
Ow!

715
00:40:18,546 --> 00:40:22,028
I'm as cute as a Powerpuff Girl.
I'll get my own show.

716
00:40:22,028 --> 00:40:23,986
Puppy power, huh?

717
00:40:23,986 --> 00:40:26,206
And he wasn't even a puppy.

718
00:40:26,206 --> 00:40:28,469
He had a gland disorder.

719
00:40:43,049 --> 00:40:46,661
Help me! Help me!
Monsters! Monsters!

720
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,671
This is the most
embarrassing thing you've done

721
00:40:56,671 --> 00:40:58,847
since you cleaned your beans
at Don Knotts' Christmas party.

722
00:41:00,588 --> 00:41:02,285
Hee-hee-hee-hee!

723
00:41:02,285 --> 00:41:03,983
How many times
do I have to tell you?

724
00:41:03,983 --> 00:41:05,506
There are no such things

725
00:41:05,506 --> 00:41:08,988
as ghouls,
ghosts, goblins, or monsters.

726
00:41:08,988 --> 00:41:11,033
Now listen up.

727
00:41:11,033 --> 00:41:12,470
There is absolutely--

728
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:16,648
absolutely no such thing as--

729
00:41:18,693 --> 00:41:21,217
Monster!

730
00:41:24,743 --> 00:41:25,700
Fred!

731
00:41:29,095 --> 00:41:30,226
FRED: Scooby....

732
00:41:32,272 --> 00:41:33,708
Save Daphne.

733
00:41:39,279 --> 00:41:40,933
My glasses.

734
00:41:40,933 --> 00:41:43,022
I can't find my glasses.

735
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:49,115
Help me find my glasses.

736
00:41:51,073 --> 00:41:53,380
Here they are.

737
00:41:53,380 --> 00:41:55,991
Thank you.

738
00:41:55,991 --> 00:41:57,123
Nice mask.

739
00:41:57,123 --> 00:42:00,430
Bad breath.

740
00:42:11,093 --> 00:42:12,094
Jinkies.

741
00:42:15,010 --> 00:42:16,446
Velma!

742
00:42:18,623 --> 00:42:19,580
Come on!

743
00:42:24,498 --> 00:42:27,327
Velma!

744
00:42:27,327 --> 00:42:30,373
This is, like, the opposite
of what I wanted to do today.

745
00:42:39,861 --> 00:42:40,819
Leave it!

746
00:42:49,262 --> 00:42:51,481
Stand back, sir.

747
00:42:51,481 --> 00:42:52,657
I'll protect you.

748
00:42:57,966 --> 00:42:59,141
Mr. Mondavarious!

749
00:43:02,928 --> 00:43:04,451
Daphne, go!

750
00:43:06,758 --> 00:43:08,934
Scooby-Doo, where are you?

751
00:43:25,037 --> 00:43:29,476
Run, suitcase.
Run, suitcase. Run--

752
00:43:58,026 --> 00:43:59,506
Thank you.

753
00:44:01,334 --> 00:44:02,422
Where's Scooby?

754
00:44:02,422 --> 00:44:03,641
I hope he's okay.

755
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:06,992
I'm here!
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

756
00:44:16,262 --> 00:44:17,872
Scooby!

757
00:44:40,678 --> 00:44:43,724
[ GRUMBLING ]

758
00:44:44,769 --> 00:44:48,381
[ ROARING ]

759
00:45:00,219 --> 00:45:01,568
I have
a sinking feeling

760
00:45:01,568 --> 00:45:04,702
these dudes aren't
brainwashed cult members.

761
00:45:04,702 --> 00:45:08,009
What do they want
with the students?

762
00:45:08,009 --> 00:45:09,402
We need to follow them.

763
00:45:09,402 --> 00:45:10,882
Say what?

764
00:45:10,882 --> 00:45:13,449
Defeat them
and save Fred and Velma.

765
00:45:13,449 --> 00:45:14,973
Sort of like my plan--

766
00:45:14,973 --> 00:45:16,496
get out of here

767
00:45:16,496 --> 00:45:19,020
and let the creatures
eat Fred and Velma.

768
00:45:19,020 --> 00:45:20,500
No way.

769
00:45:20,500 --> 00:45:22,850
Fred and Velma
always figured out everything.

770
00:45:22,850 --> 00:45:24,069
Now it's our turn.

771
00:45:24,069 --> 00:45:25,766
For the first time,

772
00:45:25,766 --> 00:45:29,465
they're the damsels in distress,
not me.

773
00:45:31,467 --> 00:45:32,642
Help?
Timber.

774
00:45:41,042 --> 00:45:43,262
Okay, I'm calling
for help.

775
00:45:43,262 --> 00:45:46,656
No. I got this.
I got this.

776
00:45:50,356 --> 00:45:52,140
I don't got this.

777
00:45:54,186 --> 00:45:55,970
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

778
00:46:01,628 --> 00:46:03,151
Coast Guard, Fitzgibbon.

779
00:46:03,151 --> 00:46:07,025
Hello, sir.
We're on Spooky Island.

780
00:46:07,025 --> 00:46:08,940
Our friends were...

781
00:46:08,940 --> 00:46:10,680
kidnapped.

782
00:46:10,680 --> 00:46:13,161
We need someone here

right away.

783
00:46:13,161 --> 00:46:15,468
We do have a unit
in the vicinity.

784
00:46:15,468 --> 00:46:17,122
Can you meet them at the pier?

785
00:46:17,122 --> 00:46:19,037
All right,
they'll be right there.

786
00:46:22,997 --> 00:46:25,130
"Our friends
have been kidnapped."

787
00:46:57,031 --> 00:46:58,598
Something messed up
is happening.

788
00:46:58,598 --> 00:47:00,339
Is the Coast Guard here?

789
00:47:01,993 --> 00:47:03,298
What happened

790
00:47:03,298 --> 00:47:05,257
to the shattered windows
and busted walls?

791
00:47:05,257 --> 00:47:07,215
Yo, red. The ball?

792
00:47:11,741 --> 00:47:12,830
Let's go.

793
00:47:28,149 --> 00:47:30,412
Anyone else
think this is strange?

794
00:47:32,762 --> 00:47:34,416
Okay, we need
to split up.

795
00:47:34,416 --> 00:47:35,722
Why?

796
00:47:35,722 --> 00:47:37,680
We need to find
Fred and Velma.

797
00:47:37,680 --> 00:47:39,204
I'll go this way.

798
00:47:39,204 --> 00:47:41,467
And we'll go with you.

799
00:47:41,467 --> 00:47:42,903
Come on, Scoob.

800
00:47:56,308 --> 00:47:58,223
♪ ...Baby ♪

801
00:47:58,223 --> 00:48:02,009
♪ I count the days
till I see you again ♪

802
00:48:02,009 --> 00:48:04,925
♪ I'm sorry ♪

803
00:48:04,925 --> 00:48:07,972
♪ One night
can make a difference ♪

804
00:48:07,972 --> 00:48:12,324
♪ Please don't leave me
hanging on and on ♪

805
00:48:12,324 --> 00:48:16,023
♪ I see the light
in your window... ♪

806
00:48:19,200 --> 00:48:21,028
Fred?

807
00:48:21,028 --> 00:48:25,163
Yo, the bitch was like, "What?"
And I was like, "Later on!"

808
00:48:25,163 --> 00:48:28,209
What up, dog?

809
00:48:28,209 --> 00:48:29,428
And...

810
00:48:29,428 --> 00:48:30,516
dog.

811
00:48:30,516 --> 00:48:33,345
Keeping it real.

812
00:48:33,345 --> 00:48:34,737
What happened last night?

813
00:48:34,737 --> 00:48:37,740
We got beats
like it was the lizz-nizz.

814
00:48:37,740 --> 00:48:39,829
You know what
I'm saying, G?

815
00:48:39,829 --> 00:48:40,830
No.

816
00:48:40,830 --> 00:48:43,224
[CRASHING]

817
00:48:43,224 --> 00:48:45,183
You hear that?

818
00:48:52,364 --> 00:48:54,366
Get the dog.

819
00:48:57,499 --> 00:48:59,197
Aha! Damsel in distress.

820
00:48:59,197 --> 00:49:01,460
Let go of me. Help!

821
00:49:03,201 --> 00:49:04,158
Hurry, get the door!

822
00:49:12,906 --> 00:49:14,386
Why is Fred in a bad mood?

823
00:49:14,386 --> 00:49:16,170
He's not in a bad mood, Scoob.

824
00:49:17,519 --> 00:49:19,608
He's a monster.

825
00:49:28,922 --> 00:49:29,967
Shaggy, bikes!

826
00:49:29,967 --> 00:49:32,447
I know, "yikes!"

827
00:49:32,447 --> 00:49:34,710
No, bikes!

828
00:49:34,710 --> 00:49:36,625
Scoob!

829
00:49:39,454 --> 00:49:41,935
Yahoo!

830
00:49:56,602 --> 00:49:57,733
Shaggy, look out!

831
00:49:59,909 --> 00:50:03,043
Something's wrong
with my friend, Beth Ann!

832
00:50:03,043 --> 00:50:04,044
Like, hop on!

833
00:50:17,840 --> 00:50:20,321
Like, what a drag!

834
00:50:32,420 --> 00:50:33,378
Like, duck!

835
00:50:55,922 --> 00:50:56,923
Yes!

836
00:50:56,923 --> 00:50:58,577
That was great!

837
00:50:58,577 --> 00:51:00,883
Are you all right?
You were great.

838
00:51:00,883 --> 00:51:01,928
You too.

839
00:51:03,147 --> 00:51:06,063
Scooby-Doo, what are you doing?

840
00:51:06,063 --> 00:51:08,500
Mary Jane
is a man in a mask.

841
00:51:08,500 --> 00:51:10,589
Mary Jane is a man in a mask?

842
00:51:10,589 --> 00:51:12,852
Scooby...

843
00:51:12,852 --> 00:51:14,897
What are you doing, man?
Step off, Scoob.

844
00:51:14,897 --> 00:51:17,161
Shaggy, you're whipped.

845
00:51:17,161 --> 00:51:18,379
I'm whipped? Yeah?

846
00:51:18,379 --> 00:51:21,252
Why don't you say that
to my face?

847
00:51:21,252 --> 00:51:24,081
Okay, I will.
Your mommy eats cat poop!

848
00:51:24,081 --> 00:51:26,866
No, Scooby-Doo,
your mom eats cat poop!

849
00:51:29,042 --> 00:51:30,391
Bring it.

850
00:51:30,391 --> 00:51:32,393
You want a piece
of the Shagster?

851
00:51:32,393 --> 00:51:34,700
Feel the pain, Scoob.

852
00:51:34,700 --> 00:51:36,963
Come on! Two shots! Two shots!

853
00:51:36,963 --> 00:51:39,661
Me and you, me and you again.

854
00:51:44,188 --> 00:51:45,624
Scoob!

855
00:51:45,624 --> 00:51:47,234
Scooby's been eaten.

856
00:51:47,234 --> 00:51:48,496
I've got to save him.

857
00:51:48,496 --> 00:51:50,281
You stay here,
I'll be right back!

858
00:51:50,281 --> 00:51:52,631
[IN A MAN'S VOICE]
No, Shaggy.

859
00:51:52,631 --> 00:51:55,286
[IN A WOMAN'S VOICE]
I mean, it's too dangerous.

860
00:51:55,286 --> 00:51:57,070
I've got to.

861
00:51:57,070 --> 00:51:59,507
He's, like, my best pal.

862
00:52:00,639 --> 00:52:01,683
Friends don't quit.

863
00:52:14,392 --> 00:52:17,177
Scoob?

864
00:52:20,441 --> 00:52:22,922
Scooby-Doo...

865
00:52:22,922 --> 00:52:24,967
where are you?

866
00:53:01,265 --> 00:53:02,918
WOMAN: Shaggy.

867
00:53:02,918 --> 00:53:05,617
Shaggy.

868
00:53:05,617 --> 00:53:07,967
Shaggy!

869
00:53:10,448 --> 00:53:11,797
Velma.

870
00:53:13,755 --> 00:53:15,540
I'll save you.

871
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:24,462
Thanks, Shaggy.

872
00:53:24,462 --> 00:53:26,159
Boy, am I glad
to see you.

873
00:53:26,159 --> 00:53:27,378
Let me go

874
00:53:27,378 --> 00:53:29,510
so I can return
to my body,

875
00:53:29,510 --> 00:53:32,034
and then get out of here
before they find you

876
00:53:32,034 --> 00:53:33,514
and steal
your protoplasm too.

877
00:53:33,514 --> 00:53:36,691
I always knew you were a hero,
Shaggy.

878
00:53:39,216 --> 00:53:41,261
Jinkies!

879
00:54:13,162 --> 00:54:14,468
Hey, buddy.

880
00:54:14,468 --> 00:54:16,165
Shaggy!

881
00:54:16,165 --> 00:54:19,473
Someone must have spiked
my root beer last night.

882
00:54:19,473 --> 00:54:22,302
Talk me down, man.
Talk me down.

883
00:54:22,302 --> 00:54:25,610
Fred, you're a frigging
protoplasmic head.

884
00:54:28,482 --> 00:54:30,049
I know,

885
00:54:30,049 --> 00:54:32,051
but I'm still the best-looking
protoplasmic head here.

886
00:54:36,882 --> 00:54:38,492
How do you
drive this thing?

887
00:54:38,492 --> 00:54:40,364
The Darkopalypse
is upon us.

888
00:54:40,364 --> 00:54:42,322
Get what you need
for the ceremony.

889
00:54:42,322 --> 00:54:45,020
On your right.
Your left.

890
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:48,197
I'm coming, good-looking!

891
00:54:51,462 --> 00:54:53,681
Thank you so much.
You've saved me.

892
00:54:53,681 --> 00:54:55,901
Sorry.
I'm looking for my friends.

893
00:54:55,901 --> 00:54:57,468
But--

894
00:55:02,821 --> 00:55:03,909
Put me back, Shaggy.

895
00:55:03,909 --> 00:55:05,780
I'll figure a way out myself.

896
00:55:05,780 --> 00:55:08,000
Like, how?

897
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:12,178
I'll use my tongue as an oar
and swim to the edge.

898
00:55:12,178 --> 00:55:13,875
Sorry.

899
00:55:29,674 --> 00:55:31,937
Yo, yo, you, yo.

900
00:55:39,510 --> 00:55:40,946
What the--

901
00:55:57,397 --> 00:55:59,399
You could use a little sunlight.

902
00:56:12,673 --> 00:56:15,850
That's one part
of the mystery solved.

903
00:56:15,850 --> 00:56:18,897
The creatures need our bodies
to survive in sunlight.

904
00:56:18,897 --> 00:56:22,074
Like a human suit.

905
00:56:22,074 --> 00:56:26,078
SPF 1,000,000.

906
00:56:26,078 --> 00:56:27,384
But what are
they doing here

907
00:56:27,384 --> 00:56:28,950
in the first place?

908
00:56:31,736 --> 00:56:33,999
Daphne, you okay?

909
00:56:33,999 --> 00:56:35,174
[IN A MAN'S VOICE]
Yeah.

910
00:56:35,174 --> 00:56:38,090
But I'm not Daphne!

911
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:39,308
Fred?

912
00:56:45,880 --> 00:56:49,536
I couldn't get to my body.
I didn't know where else to go.

913
00:56:49,536 --> 00:56:53,453
It's not easy to steer
when you're pure spirit.

914
00:56:56,891 --> 00:56:59,720
I can look at myself naked.

915
00:56:59,720 --> 00:57:01,200
Oh, brother.

916
00:57:09,382 --> 00:57:11,340
DAPHNE'S VOICE:
Get your hands off me.

917
00:57:11,340 --> 00:57:12,733
Daphne?

918
00:57:12,733 --> 00:57:15,214
He planned this
somehow, didn't he?

919
00:57:15,214 --> 00:57:17,085
Hey, good-looking.

920
00:57:18,173 --> 00:57:20,567
Fred, you egocentric--

921
00:57:20,567 --> 00:57:22,351
Please tell me
you guys are you.

922
00:57:22,351 --> 00:57:24,528
Fred keeps touching me.

923
00:57:24,528 --> 00:57:28,227
Kind of makes you nostalgic
for the homicidal creatures.

924
00:57:28,227 --> 00:57:31,317
I stole this.
I hope it helps.

925
00:57:31,317 --> 00:57:32,927
The Daemon Ritus.

926
00:57:38,542 --> 00:57:41,066
Hey, I'm me again.

927
00:57:41,066 --> 00:57:43,068
[AS VELMA]
Yippee for you.

928
00:57:43,068 --> 00:57:46,724
[AS SHAGGY]
Why am I wearing a dress?

929
00:57:46,724 --> 00:57:48,465
[AS FRED] Everyone remain calm.

930
00:57:48,465 --> 00:57:50,684
Velma, what the heck's going on?

931
00:57:50,684 --> 00:57:52,512
[AS VELMA] If I am correct,

932
00:57:52,512 --> 00:57:54,993
due to the instability
of protoplasm

933
00:57:54,993 --> 00:57:57,125
in the proximity
of the Daemon Ritus,

934
00:57:57,125 --> 00:58:01,303
we're going to continue
randomly changing bodies until--

935
00:58:06,091 --> 00:58:08,223
[AS VELMA] Until the protoplasm
realigns with the right bodies.

936
00:58:08,223 --> 00:58:10,138
[AS DAPHNE] I'm Fred again!

937
00:58:10,138 --> 00:58:13,533
[AS SHAGGY]
Daph, what's wrong with you?

938
00:58:13,533 --> 00:58:14,795
Don't you ever eat?

939
00:58:20,627 --> 00:58:21,933
I'm me.

940
00:58:21,933 --> 00:58:23,064
DAPHNE: I'm back.

941
00:58:23,064 --> 00:58:25,023
Like, me too.

942
00:58:25,023 --> 00:58:26,024
Told you so.

943
00:58:26,024 --> 00:58:26,981
[EXPLOSION]

944
00:58:26,981 --> 00:58:27,982
Oh, no.

945
00:58:27,982 --> 00:58:28,983
Let's go.

946
00:58:32,639 --> 00:58:36,600
Something tells me
that was the wrong ingredient.

947
00:58:36,600 --> 00:58:38,297
Wait.

948
00:58:38,297 --> 00:58:41,779
I know
how to handle this guy.

949
00:58:41,779 --> 00:58:43,998
Hey, you! What're you doing?

950
00:58:43,998 --> 00:58:46,305
Yes. That is
masterful.

951
00:58:46,305 --> 00:58:48,612
I'm trying to do a voodoo
ritual, if you don't mind.

952
00:58:48,612 --> 00:58:51,484
It's important to get
the right ingredients.

953
00:58:51,484 --> 00:58:53,094
The only way I can
protect myself

954
00:58:53,094 --> 00:58:56,489
is by blessing
this dead Arnouki beast.

955
00:58:56,489 --> 00:58:59,797
They're about to perform
their evil Darkopalypse ritual.

956
00:58:59,797 --> 00:59:00,928
Darkopalypse ritual?

957
00:59:00,928 --> 00:59:02,451
That's right.

958
00:59:02,451 --> 00:59:04,628
That's what
the ancient text describes.

959
00:59:04,628 --> 00:59:08,153
Don't open that!

960
00:59:08,153 --> 00:59:10,024
They use the protoplasm
as an energy source.

961
00:59:10,024 --> 00:59:14,115
And the leader needs to absorb
a purely good soul

962
00:59:14,115 --> 00:59:15,552
to complete the ritual.

963
00:59:15,552 --> 00:59:18,729
Legend has it,
once the ritual is performed,

964
00:59:18,729 --> 00:59:20,818
the creatures
will rule on Earth

965
00:59:20,818 --> 00:59:22,950
for 10,000 years.

966
00:59:22,950 --> 00:59:24,952
That's why
I have this in my house.

967
00:59:24,952 --> 00:59:26,475
To protect myself.

968
00:59:26,475 --> 00:59:28,086
You have another one of those?

969
00:59:28,086 --> 00:59:30,654
DAPHNE: Those creatures
are taking over the world?

970
00:59:30,654 --> 00:59:33,831
That is so mean!

971
00:59:33,831 --> 00:59:36,660
They can't do it
without a pure human soul.

972
00:59:36,660 --> 00:59:38,662
Where will they get one?

973
00:59:38,662 --> 00:59:40,533
I didn't say human.

974
00:59:40,533 --> 00:59:43,841
Oh, boy.

975
00:59:43,841 --> 00:59:45,930
[WHIMPERS]

976
01:00:01,467 --> 01:00:04,339
Hello, puppy.

977
01:00:04,339 --> 01:00:08,430
If the person behind all this
needs Scooby-Doo....

978
01:00:08,430 --> 01:00:10,955
Then that person is the one
who brought Scooby here.

979
01:00:14,828 --> 01:00:16,308
Scoobert!

980
01:00:16,308 --> 01:00:19,093
How are you, my friend?

981
01:00:19,093 --> 01:00:20,965
Sit down, please.

982
01:00:20,965 --> 01:00:24,795
Okay.

983
01:00:24,795 --> 01:00:26,318
Scooby Snack?

984
01:00:26,318 --> 01:00:28,059
Maybe one.

985
01:00:33,064 --> 01:00:35,240
We'll need
some more of those.

986
01:00:35,240 --> 01:00:38,765
That's me!

987
01:00:38,765 --> 01:00:44,075
It certainly is.
And that's because...why?

988
01:00:44,075 --> 01:00:47,034
We love you, Scooby-Doo.

989
01:00:47,034 --> 01:00:51,125
Unlike that
alleged friend of yours, Shaggy.

990
01:00:51,125 --> 01:00:54,302
He wouldn't believe you

991
01:00:54,302 --> 01:00:56,522
about that nasty girl,
Mary Jane,

992
01:00:56,522 --> 01:00:57,741
would he?

993
01:00:57,741 --> 01:01:01,092
No.

994
01:01:01,092 --> 01:01:04,008
But I believe you,
my friend.

995
01:01:04,008 --> 01:01:05,618
And that's why I've got

996
01:01:05,618 --> 01:01:09,100
a very important job
for you.

997
01:01:09,100 --> 01:01:11,015
What's that?

998
01:01:11,015 --> 01:01:12,494
That's a cat
with a bobbing head.

999
01:01:12,494 --> 01:01:14,322
Please don't touch it.

1000
01:01:14,322 --> 01:01:18,805
Scooby, I would like you...

1001
01:01:18,805 --> 01:01:22,591
to be a sacrifice.

1002
01:01:22,591 --> 01:01:25,159
A sacrifice?

1003
01:01:28,772 --> 01:01:30,338
If Mondorajagaga
wanted Scooby,

1004
01:01:30,338 --> 01:01:32,993
why'd he invite us?

1005
01:01:32,993 --> 01:01:35,517
It doesn't matter.
We've got to go save Scoob.

1006
01:01:35,517 --> 01:01:37,171
Our area of expertise

1007
01:01:37,171 --> 01:01:39,478
is nut jobs
in Halloween costumes.

1008
01:01:39,478 --> 01:01:41,698
We're supposed to be heroes.

1009
01:01:42,916 --> 01:01:47,094
So I'm going to do
what I always do.

1010
01:01:47,094 --> 01:01:49,575
I'm going to eat myself
a Scooby Snack,

1011
01:01:49,575 --> 01:01:51,446
and I'm going to save
my best pal.

1012
01:01:54,014 --> 01:01:56,147
FRED: Velmster?

1013
01:01:56,147 --> 01:01:58,889
You think
I'm going to fall for that?

1014
01:01:58,889 --> 01:02:00,891
Giving me my own nickname?

1015
01:02:02,196 --> 01:02:07,941
Trying to make me feel
like part of the gang?

1016
01:02:09,900 --> 01:02:11,510
We could make a plan.

1017
01:02:11,510 --> 01:02:13,468
What can I do?

1018
01:02:13,468 --> 01:02:15,862
The only thing I'm good for
is getting caught.

1019
01:02:15,862 --> 01:02:19,039
But you never let that
stop you before.

1020
01:02:19,039 --> 01:02:22,303
And if that's not a true hero,
then I don't know what is.

1021
01:02:32,313 --> 01:02:35,490
Let's get jinkie with it.

1022
01:03:09,350 --> 01:03:12,092
Okay, so we use the pulleys
to tip over the vat.

1023
01:03:12,092 --> 01:03:14,399
VELMA:
Daphne will open the air vents

1024
01:03:14,399 --> 01:03:16,880
and release the disco skull.

1025
01:03:16,880 --> 01:03:19,230
The light will refract off it--

1026
01:03:19,230 --> 01:03:20,753
The creatures will explode,

1027
01:03:20,753 --> 01:03:23,582
I'll find Scoob,
and we'll have saved the world!

1028
01:03:23,582 --> 01:03:27,194
FRED:
Oh, no. The ritual's beginning.

1029
01:03:27,194 --> 01:03:28,239
Quick!

1030
01:03:28,239 --> 01:03:29,806
Attach this to the vat!

1031
01:03:39,511 --> 01:03:40,860
We're here to save you!

1032
01:03:40,860 --> 01:03:42,601
VELMA:
Shaggy, faster.

1033
01:03:42,601 --> 01:03:43,950
All systems go!

1034
01:03:45,517 --> 01:03:47,084
Wait, no!

1035
01:03:47,084 --> 01:03:48,737
Mystery Inc. rides again.

1036
01:04:19,464 --> 01:04:21,031
Quick! Hide the Daemon Ritus!

1037
01:04:33,478 --> 01:04:35,306
Would you like
another Scooby Snack?

1038
01:04:35,306 --> 01:04:38,613
Okay.

1039
01:04:38,613 --> 01:04:41,747
Scooby-Doo!

1040
01:04:50,408 --> 01:04:52,801
♪ This is
what we creatures sing ♪

1041
01:05:02,202 --> 01:05:05,902
♪ This is
what we creatures sing ♪

1042
01:05:58,041 --> 01:06:01,044
Yo, yo, yo. Yo, homedogs!

1043
01:06:01,044 --> 01:06:03,568
Y'all forgot
the next part of the dance,

1044
01:06:03,568 --> 01:06:06,963
where we do
the electric slide, you know?

1045
01:06:10,575 --> 01:06:13,273
♪ And back it on up
and drive the bus ♪

1046
01:06:13,273 --> 01:06:15,275
♪ Drive the bus and stop ♪

1047
01:06:15,275 --> 01:06:18,365
♪ And back it up... ♪♪

1048
01:06:18,365 --> 01:06:20,977
Hurry up, Velma.

1049
01:06:20,977 --> 01:06:25,111
Welcome to my little
end-of-the-world party.

1050
01:06:25,111 --> 01:06:29,246
I've waited a long time
for this moment.

1051
01:06:29,246 --> 01:06:34,207
Thank you for returning
the ultimate party favor:

1052
01:06:34,207 --> 01:06:36,166
The Daemon Ritus.

1053
01:06:39,169 --> 01:06:42,650
And now, behold the sacrifice.

1054
01:06:45,088 --> 01:06:48,047
Thank you. Thank you.

1055
01:06:48,047 --> 01:06:50,006
Hello. Thank you.

1056
01:06:52,051 --> 01:06:54,227
Thank you. Shaggy?

1057
01:06:57,839 --> 01:06:58,971
Let's run for it.

1058
01:06:58,971 --> 01:07:00,407
We've got to
get out of here.

1059
01:07:00,407 --> 01:07:01,930
I'm a sacrifice.

1060
01:07:01,930 --> 01:07:03,584
A sacrifice?

1061
01:07:03,584 --> 01:07:05,934
Dude,
that's not a good thing, Scoob.

1062
01:07:10,939 --> 01:07:14,247
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

1063
01:07:14,247 --> 01:07:15,509
And I'm sorry

1064
01:07:15,509 --> 01:07:17,163
I haven't been
a very good friend

1065
01:07:17,163 --> 01:07:18,469
since we got here.

1066
01:07:18,469 --> 01:07:20,514
But you've got to trust me now.

1067
01:07:20,514 --> 01:07:22,168
You don't trust me!

1068
01:07:22,168 --> 01:07:23,604
I do trust you.

1069
01:07:23,604 --> 01:07:27,652
Now, look.
Who's your best buddy?

1070
01:07:29,393 --> 01:07:30,394
